@casualjim BTW, can I let go-swagger skip generating `Validate()` method for the request body?
```sh
var body v1.ThirdPartyObject
if err := body.Validate(route.Formats); err != nil {   
				res = append(res, err)
}
```

@YanzhaoLi  go-swagger expects all models to implement the `github.com/go-openapi/runtime.Validatable` interface.
You can always embed your third-party object in your own definition like shown below and refer to that redefined type in your spec.

```go
type MyThirdPartyObject struct {
  ThirdPartyObject
}

func (m MyThirdPartyObject)  Validate(_ strfmt.Registry) error {
  return nil
}
```
